---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import AppShell from '../../components/layout/AppShell.astro';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/seo';
import PageHeader from '../../components/shared/PageHeader.astro';
import Prose from '../../components/shared/Prose.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy — ToolBox Image"
  description="ToolBox Image runs entirely in your browser. No uploads, no tracking, no accounts. Your images never leave your device."
  schemas={[
    breadcrumbSchema([
      { name: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { name: 'Privacy', href: '/legal/privacy' },
    ]),
  ]}
>
  <AppShell>
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container-narrow stack stack-lg">
        <PageHeader
          eyebrow="Privacy"
          title="Your images stay on your device."
          lead="Privacy is not a feature we added. It is the architecture. Here is how and why."
        />

        <Prose>
          <h2>1. No uploads. Ever.</h2>
          <p>
            ToolBox Image runs entirely in your browser. Every step —
            decoding, resizing, recompressing, encoding — happens on your
            device using WebAssembly and the native canvas. Your image data
            never leaves your device, never touches a server, and is never
            shared with third parties.
          </p>

          <h2>2. No tracking. No cookies.</h2>
          <p>
            We do not set tracking cookies, do not fingerprint your device,
            and do not use third-party analytics on this site. The only
            thing we store is your theme preference (light, dark, or
            system) in your browser's <code>localStorage</code>.
          </p>
          <p>
            You can verify this yourself. Open DevTools → Network → reload
            the page. Every request is for static assets served from our
            CDN. There are no analytics endpoints, no pixel beacons, no
            third-party requests.
          </p>

          <h2>3. No accounts required.</h2>
          <p>
            There is nothing to sign up for. Every tool is free, unlimited,
            and works the moment you open the page. We will never ask for
            your email address.
          </p>

          <h2>4. No fingerprinting.</h2>
          <p>
            We do not collect your IP address beyond what our CDN's raw
            logs record (standard HTTP, no application-level processing).
            We do not read your User-Agent beyond what the browser sends
            by default. We do not use canvas fingerprinting, font
            enumeration, or any other browser-side identification technique.
          </p>

          <h2>5. The one thing we do store.</h2>
          <p>
            Your theme preference (<code>light</code>, <code>dark</code>, or
            <code>system</code>) is stored in your browser's localStorage
            under the key <code>toolbox-theme</code>. This never leaves your
            device. You can clear it at any time from your browser settings.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Open by default.</h2>
          <p>
            Our compression engine is built on open standards (WebAssembly,
            Canvas, the browser's native decoders). You can verify this
            yourself in DevTools.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Changes to this policy.</h2>
          <p>
            If we ever change anything material about how your data is
            handled, we will post a notice on this page and update the
            date below. The current architecture — entirely client-side —
            is the foundation of the product, so we do not anticipate any
            breaking changes here.
          </p>

          <h2>8. Contact.</h2>
          <p>
            Questions or concerns? <a href="/contact/">Get in touch</a> — we
            read every message.
          </p>

          <hr />
          <p style="color:var(--color-mute);font-size:var(--text-caption);">
            Last updated: June 2026.
          </p>
        </Prose>
      </div>
    </section>
  </AppShell>
</Layout>